TopicTitle: New Mun Easter Egg - Schiaparelli's Impact

Articles.Content:
I just started using the KerbalNet to look for Easter Eggs.

I  went here to see if it was listed in wiki and it was not. (http://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/List_of_easter_eggs)

Mun - Schiaparelli's Impact

Latitude: -9.83569712969825

Longitude: 25.9216365170866

Altitude: 1470.4854433143

 

Images located here: ( http://imgur.com/a/Jbtfl )
Is it green tinged? If it is, one randomly spawns for each game on each body, in different places.
What do you mean by Green tinged?
I dont think its an easter egg, I think its just a waypoint name. They are randomly generated when you create them
Yeah, waypoint names are random. I think i´ve got 'Schiaparelli's Impact' on Kerbin once

I googled it up.  It should be on Duna (Mars), not the mun.

Is there ever a chance I will be able to scan a mun Easter Egg

 

LOL, I also noticed I put 2016 as my plaque date.   Now I have to go back to the mun and replace the flag. :-P
